        <div class="body">
            <p>This is done because of AcceptPathInfo directive of Apache.</p>

<p>Persons who cant use mod_rewrite can use this directive to jump over the index.php and make it part of the baseUrl.
As an exemple :
<a href="http://somehost/route/from/here">http://somehost/route/from/here</a> works when mod_rewrite is activated
<a href="http://somehost/indexbootstrap.php/route/from/here">http://somehost/indexbootstrap.php/route/from/here</a> works when mod_rewrite is not activated but acceptPathInfo turned to on</p>

